.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Continuous Monitoring and Enforcement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
ECIO shall deploy automated mechanisms to dynamically monitor systems for deviations from their approved DISA STIG or CIS baselines.
 When automated tools detect a deviation,
 the system shall generate an alert to the Assistant IT Director and the respective Systems or Network Administrator.
 Critical-risk deviations shall be remediated,
 or the affected asset logically isolated from the production network,
 within four (4) hours of detection.
 High-risk deviations shall be remediated within twenty-four (24) hours of detection.
 Deviations not remediated within the required timeframe shall be escalated to the IT Director and documented as an open exception in accordance with Section 4.
\end_layout

